 Capt. Khanyisile Zwane said that two fatal pedestrian accidents were reported at around 20:30 on Sunday. One occurred near the Alzu Petroport and the other at the Bethal off-ramp. In the first incident, a pedestrian was run over by a white BMW near the Petroport. The person was declared dead on the scene. During the second incident, a woman drove to the police station to report an accident after she felt her vehicle hitting something on the N4. She did not want to stop at the scene alone. Also read: Four young lives lost after horror crash in Middelburg Police escorted the woman to the scene where they discovered the body of a man lying next to the road. Signs indicate that the man was killed prior to the accident the woman reported. He had a head wound of which the blood had already dried and a swollen waist. A yellow car mirror and a Samsung phone was discovered next to the body. Capt. Zwane said that neither of the two deceased have been identified yet and that police could not find any identification on them. The Middelburg Police are investigating two cases of culpable homicide.  R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za